  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Surgical trauma triggers a massive inflammatory response. Over time, both the innate and
      adaptive branches of the immune system are affected by surgical trauma. The purpose of this
      study is to use a single cell flow cytometry approach to characterize the cellular and
      molecular mechanisms involved in the inflammatory response to surgical trauma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
